    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Japan)/10–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-04">October 4,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 8—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. As there appears to be considerable discussion among politically-minded
                    Japanese in regard to question of the revision of Japanese Constitution it is
                    suggested that completion of the directive on this subject be expedited as much
                    as possible. Meanwhile please telegraph outline of draft so that we may know
                    direction which American Government thought is taking in the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
